This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel method for generating superpixels, which is a fundamental step in many image pattern recognition tasks. The paper also discusses the suitability of the proposed method for video segmentation, which is a common application of computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and segmentation, which are important tasks in multimedia applications. 

The machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes an adaptive method for generating superpixels, which involves clustering edges extracted from the image objects. This clustering process can be seen as a form of unsupervised learning. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is another possibility as the paper proposes a new method for solving a specific problem in image analysis, which can be seen as a subfield of AI. 

Finally, the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with image segmentation, which is an important task in computer graphics.
